cjnIpIfMgmt.name: cjnIpIfMgmt
cjnIpIfMgmt.contactinfo: Erick Crowell -- ecrowell@lucent.com Ira Steckler -- isteckler@lucent.com
cjnIpIfMgmt.description: Cajun Private IP Interface Management MIB

cjnIpIfNextIndex.name: cjnIpIfNextIndex
cjnIpIfNextIndex.description: The next available IfIndex. This number should be used to create new rows in the IpIfTable

cjnIpIfTable.name: cjnIpIfTable
cjnIpIfTable.description: A list of Cajun IP interface entries. The number of entries is given by the value of cjnIpIfNumber.

cjnIpIfIndex.name: cjnIpIfIndex
cjnIpIfIndex.description: The globally unique identifier for this interface. This number MUST correlate with the IfTable's IfIndex in MIB-II or RFC2233

cjnIpIfRowStatus.name: cjnIpIfRowStatus
cjnIpIfRowStatus.description: The Status of this entry in the table. Note the available states: active(1), -- Obviously Active. notInService(2) -- Interface configured but disabled. notReady(3), -- Interface NOT configured. createAndGo(4), createAndWait(5) or destroy(6)

cjnIpIfIpAddress.name: cjnIpIfIpAddress
cjnIpIfIpAddress.description: The IP Address associated with this IP interface.

cjnIpIfIpSubnetMask.name: cjnIpIfIpSubnetMask
cjnIpIfIpSubnetMask.description: The IP Subnet Mask associated with this IP interface.

cjnIpIfMacFormat.name: cjnIpIfMacFormat
cjnIpIfMacFormat.description: The ethernet framing type used on this IP interface.

cjnIpIfVlanIfIndex.name: cjnIpIfVlanIfIndex
cjnIpIfVlanIfIndex.description: The interface index of the VLAN or Ethernet or Serial console for this interface. This number MUST correlate with the IfTable's IfIndex in MIB-II or RFC2233.

cjnIpIfName.name: cjnIpIfName
cjnIpIfName.description: The protocol Unique name associated with this interface. This name is limited to 32 characters and may appear in other protocol interface entry such as IPX, Appletalk but MAY NOT be duplicated within the cjnIpIfTable. In otherwords other protocols can use this interface name but IP may only have this name associated with one interface.

cjnIpIfIpRouting.name: cjnIpIfIpRouting
cjnIpIfIpRouting.description: The Consumption / Forwarding mode assocated with this IP Interface. The RoutingAndMgmt mode enables IP Routing and local Packet consumption. The MgmtOnly mode disables IP Forwarding but continues to allow local Packet consumption on this interface. The routingOnly mode is disables Local Packet consumption but continues to allow IP Forwarding on this interface

cjnIpIfSpoofCheckEnabled.name: cjnIpIfSpoofCheckEnabled
cjnIpIfSpoofCheckEnabled.description: This feature is not supported at this time.

cjnIpIfProxyArpEnabled.name: cjnIpIfProxyArpEnabled
cjnIpIfProxyArpEnabled.description: enables / disables Proxy Arp functionality on this interface.

cjnIpIfIcmpRedirEnabled.name: cjnIpIfIcmpRedirEnabled
cjnIpIfIcmpRedirEnabled.description: enables / disables Icmp Redirect messages from originating from this interface.

cjnIpIfUdpRbcastMode.name: cjnIpIfUdpRbcastMode
cjnIpIfUdpRbcastMode.description: configures the NetBIOS UDP Rebroadcast mode on this interface.

cjnIpIfAdminStatus.name: cjnIpIfAdminStatus
cjnIpIfAdminStatus.description: The administrative state of this interface.

cjnIpIfStatus.name: cjnIpIfStatus
cjnIpIfStatus.description: The current state of this interface.

cjnIpIfBootpDhcpGateway.name: cjnIpIfBootpDhcpGateway
cjnIpIfBootpDhcpGateway.description: Enable or disable the designation of this interface as that which will 'receive' BOOTP/DHCP requests with a source IP address of 0.0.0.0. This is used on a multinetted interface when it is otherwise ambiguous as to which interface 'receives' the request, and is important because the IP address of the receiving interface is inserted into the giaddr field of the request before the request is relayed to the BOOTP/DHCP server. If this attribute is disabled, then: - if only one IP interface exists on a VLAN, that IP address is inserted into the request - if more than one IP address exists on a VLAN, the router will choose an interface If more than one IP interface on a given VLAN has this attribute enabled, the router will choose an interface among those with the attribute enabled.
